name: Harvey Glover
desc: This laptop is awesome. Love it.Would give them 4stars for customer service ordered a gpu paid for next day delivery and wasn’t dispatched was told I would get the delivery refunded but that never happened. Do not care once they have your money no phone call to say it’s been delayed that’s all it would take to keep your customers happy especially when charging over rrp for a gpuWould give them 0stars for customer service ordered a gpu paid for next day delivery and wasn’t dispatched was told I would get the delivery refunded but that never happened. Do not care once they have your money no phone call to say it’s been delayed that’s all it would take to keep your customers happy especially when charging over rrp for a gpu.

Nice laptop. Love it.Purchased an AMD 5700G from Ebuyer which arrived today. Upon unboxing, noticed that a pin was slightly bent in the corner. Assuming the product would be in working order when I received it, I chanced my arm at putting it into the PC to see what would happen, of course that was to no avail. Upon calling customer service, I was met with a rude technician who from the start of the call, sounded like he couldn't care less about my issue.
name: Joann Hughes
Neva Scott
desc: Awesome performance. Highly recomended. I’ll leave it to the reader to decide the stars. Due to urgency I made a quick purchase of Lexmark MC3224 printer for our busy office. Bought it on the 6th July 2021 after couple of days it had to be returned due to software and a problem with the duplex system.

name: Schwartz Blake
desc: Not so good battery backup. Bought CPU for Son as a present in November. Come to install it and found one of the pins was bent in the packaging. Ebuyer keep stating they only offer returns on unopened items and refuse to offer refund or replacement. Avoid!

name: West Mcclure
desc: Overall okay. Not good and not bad. DO NOT USE EBUYER. After having paid for next day delivery the product was delayed. Upon calling they confirmed there was an internal issue and pushed the order through. The product never came even though it was marked down as delivered. There was never any proof of delivery provided and they are unwilling to provide a refund. £114.38 including next day delivery FOR NOTHING. DO NOT USE EBUYER.

name: Lily Jarvis
desc: Great laptop in a low price. Wiggle out of warranties Bought a Asus GPU from Ebuyer, all was well until it started drawing to much power, burnt out 5 HDMI cables, melted paint off the back of my case, gave off sparks and HDMI ports died. Asus do not deal with issues and said to send it back to the retailer.

name: Josefina Wiggins
desc: The battery backup should be improved. On 26th November, I ordered a CPU and motherboard for £592.95. This is a fair amount of money for me to spend on these items. The website said that the motherboard awaiting stock which was due in 26th November. I was able to select a delivery date of 29th November for this order.

name: Allison Callahan
desc: I am satisfied with this. But then storage is low. Ordered 3 times from them in the last month - website and voice says they are shipping as normal BUT .....they use Yodel - every order paid for next day delivery and every order turned out to be 'next week' delivery, 8 days, 3 days and now been waiting for 7 days on the last order. WHY do large firms use the worlds worst delivery firm just because they are the cheapest, especially when they can pick and pack an order within an hour of getting it, only to be let down by their courier!!

name: Nielsen Kennedy
desc: I liked this product and I will buy one more for my Jantush. Really disappointed with what the company's after-sale process and customer service. This is a shopfront and while the buying process is quite good after you paid for the order the troubles begin.

name: Vicky Crawford
desc: Fantastic performance. Loved it. Disappointed that lenovo laptop failed to function after 8 months. Following a failed attempt at repair I spoke with Jake Colley at Ebuyer. He was extremely efficient, very pleasant and although he had to get a sanction from management, a refund was agreed. (I have yet to receive it but it is only days and the faulty machine is being returned tomo) If there is a problem I feel I could get back to him.

name: Sheree Berg
desc: Nice laptop. Love it. I've had an account with Ebuyer for over 10 years. A few weeks ago I bought the highest-spec laptop on the market from them for £3000. When the parcel arrived, it was empty - the laptop peripherals (charger etc) were still inside. But no laptop!

name: Jerri Manning
desc: It is good low budget laptop. My package was sent to the wrong address. E-buyer and the shipper were informed of this before delivery. They obviously received the notification but nevertheless delivered half the order to the wrong address (despite a requirement for my signature which they didn't have) and tell me I will have to wait for two weeks or more for the remainder of the order to be delivered to me
